    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2002 BMW M5 (E39), a definitive benchmark in high-performance sedan engineering. This example is powered by the S62 4.9L V8, featuring individual throttle bodies and double-VANOS variable valve timing, delivering a seamless power band and exceptional throttle response. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 420G six-speed manual gearbox and a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential, ensuring precise torque management. The chassis maintains its original structural integrity, with the suspension system exhibiting zero bushing deflection and factory-spec damping rates. Comprehensive maintenance records confirm a recent overhaul of the cooling system and the high-pressure VANOS lines. The exterior finish remains deep and lustrous, while the interior features impeccable Nappa leather and a pixel-perfect instrument cluster. This is a mechanically transparent, turn-key enthusiast vehicle for the collector who demands peak atmospheric performance.",
